All orders are charged per bag, each bag is $20. A bag is either our supplied ClothesLyne laundry bags or any tall kitchen garbage Are lights and darks separated? Lights and colors are only separated if specified in the order details page while placing your Is there a minimum price per order? Yes, the minimum order price is $20. Who will be washing our clothes? Service providers are either established laundromats or freelancers who are vetted and trained by A way we like to explain the freelancers is by comparing them to Uber and Doordash When will I receive my laundry back? Our standard delivery time is hours after pick up, but we offer hour delivery for an added What laundry detergents do we offer? We offer multiple different types of laundry detergent, fabric softener, and dryer We offer hypoallergenic, organic, and unscented options Do we offer dry cleaning? Unfortunately, ClothesLyne does not offer dry cleaning at this time, but we look to add this service in the Do we train and inspect our service providers? Yes, ClothesLyne takes serious consideration on who we allow being a service provider on our All service providers complete training before being allowed to accept New Service providers are inspected to ensure they have the proper facilities to efficiently and cleanly perform laundry What temperature are the clothes washed in? Cold, all loads are washed cold unless requested What happens if my clothes are misplaced or damaged? Our customer support team would be glad to help and determine an optimal solution for Do I need to be home for delivery or pick up? No, we’re all about Just put your clothes out after your order and go on with your What time is pick up and delivery? Pick up and delivery occurs between 6 pm unless you pay additional costs for a customer pickup Do clothes get mixed with other orders? NO! Clothes are never mixed together with other All orders are tagged and separated to ensure they never Do we wash larger items? Yes, we offer large item wash, which includes dog beds, comforters, and Can I communicate with my ClothesLyner? Yes, you can communicate with the ClothesLyner at any point of the service being carried The chat is easily found in your order details Is my identity and payment information protected? Yes, all information identity and payment information are processed through Stripe payment What if it’s raining when my clothes are returned? Your clothes will be protected in a waterproof bag and placed where the elements can’t affect Can I request a hypoallergenic detergent? Yes, of ClothessLyne offers hypoallergenic, organic, and unscented Being a ClothesLyner What do I need to get started? Washer and dryer, drying rack, clothesline, or something to hang dry clothes, laundry detergent, clear plastic bags, laundry baskets, and a How can I get more orders? Being a clotheslyner in an established market is very The more orders you complete, the higher ratings you How many active orders can I have? There are no limits to the number of As long as you can handle the workload of the laundry you will not stop receiving an order unless you’re Extra add ons? You must offer our required add ons, but the recommended ones you do Offering recommended will allow you to receive more orders and make more cash money! Do I wash in hot or cold water? Cold unless otherwise instructed by the customer in the order Dryer temp? Never set the dryer to high It will ruin specific garments, and customers will file a claim against Instead, use medium If your customer includes delicates, which will be indicated in your app, use low heat on What’s the delivery and deadline? The deadline for pickup and delivery is hours depending on your You can deliver the order back early at the scheduled time with the Can I extend the deadline? Only with the customer’s What happens if I miss a deadline? Suspension or removal from the ClothesLyne Pick up and Drop off hours? am and 6 pm ar the standard times can choose custom times which can be any time between our two standard time Custom times will result in increased pay for the service About Folding Folding Guidelines: Clothes must be folded right after the dry cycle ends to avoid wrinkled Follow our folding ClothesLyne Do your best to match Button and Zip up clothes if possible Folding is wher

ClipDart’s concept came to me via my own mental health struggles while attending Grinnell College in Being an from the south side of Chicago, I never had an issue finding a barber for the first years of my If my barber was not available, I could easily locate another nearby barber without any in the cultural Then, I moved to the middle of Iowa and I was not able to find a barber within hours who was skilled at cutting minority hair This is when I truly realized how essential hair practitioners are to one’s mental Within most minority communities, barbers are viewed as therapists, mentors, and pillars of the The barbershop is a and cultural institution within black and brown communities where generations after generations share stories, unpack struggles, and listen to life’s It is a safe This continual mental struggle of feeling as if my culture was not included became one of the main reasons why I transferred after three years with just one more year until At ClipDart, we continually create innovative strategies to prevent individuals from experiencing the same mental adversity that I went Our mission to is to make a powerful, positive impact on the mental wellness of communities around the world through hair practitioners, while, concurrently, revolutionizing the hair industry & common view of hair practitioners Today, ClipDart Barbers around the world cultivate equitable, cultural spaces within (and with) our struggling communities via their very unique and valuable We are certainly the future of haircare! Blaustein join forces to establish SBMHC In , Jaime Blaustein, a drug addict who had been declared “hopeless” by number of prominent doctors and experts, boarded a plane to South Florida en route to his rehab in 3 It was here that he met Ben Brafman, owner of Destination Hope and a widely recognized mental health Jaime’s Second Chance Jaime ultimately had not reached his bottom and could not stay He was dismissed from Ben’s treatment center after several Over the next three years, Jaime’s life consisted of hospitals, overdoses, legal trouble, emotional turmoil and strained family But on Christmas Day of , Jaime experienced the miracle of surrender and found a solution that had been so He was catapulted into a brand new life with the right guidance, the willingness to do the necessary work to recover and, eventually, rigorous work with others who struggle with mental health and substance The Comeback Jaime was given a second chance at life – his internal condition was brought to a place of contentment he didn’t even know He resurrected his career, repaired all of his relationships that were previously neglected, and became a sponsor to dozens of men in His family was able to sleep at night knowing he was not only recovered, but In , he was accepted to Duke University’s MBA program, where he went on to lead the investment banking club, travel the world, make friends, and continue to live by his primary purpose of helping others along the Following Duke, Jaime moved to New York City and started work on Wall Street as an investment banker for Credit Suisse, focusing on mergers & acquisitions, divestitures, leveraged buyouts, restructurings and various debt and equity financings within the Industrials His new life failed to even resemble that of a struggling But deep down, he had a desire to further align his life with his passion of helping others recover from the depths of despair and experience a second chance at a In South Florida, meanwhile, Ben Brafman had continued successfully operating Destination Hope, helping thousands of patients with mental disorders and He continued to build his national presence as a respected authority on mental He had been watching Jaime’s progress from afar on social media and got a gut feeling that the two of them may be able to develop something uniquely special So in early , Ben called Jaime to see if he had any interest in establishing a behavioral health center focusing primarily on mental health and also leveraging their collective experience helping addicts recover from On the verge of a promotion to investment banking Vice President, Jaime hesitated before getting quiet with this big decision for a few It became clear what the right decision was, and that his experience could be much more Posted in News Private Sale Vehicle Purchases Posted on November , November , Recent challenges with inventory have made it difficult to find both new and used vehicles on the dealership Did you know that Credit Union can set you up with a car loan, even when you’re buying from a private seller? Buying from a private seller instead of a dealer can help you get the best price on a used You’ll need to do some extra research to ensure you’re getting a good deal, but it can pay off in the long Figure out how much money you can spend each month on a car Then, stop in at Credit Union to speak with a member of our lending We’ll be able help you identify how much you can afford to buy to stick with your budgeted monthly We’ll consider current rates, your credit score, car value, and other factors before determining how much you qualify This process is called It helps you when you, the buyer, negotiate a sales price with the Next, peruse online classifieds until you find a vehicle you Check out the local newspaper, and other online sale platforms (social media). Arrange to meet the seller in a public place—and take someone with you for safety If you like how the car drives and looks, ask the seller about the vehicle’s Finally, get a report (we can do this for you here at the Credit ) and have a reputable mechanic take a look at it before you One of the biggest benefits of buying from a private seller is the opportunity to negotiate price, so be fair but don’t be Once you’ve settled on a price, put the terms in Then contact us here at Credit Union, and we’ll run the numbers to make sure this deal will work for Your Loan Officer will be able to provide you with the next steps to finalizing the purchase, such as a copy of the vehicle title or a payoff letter from the current lien We’re here to help you every step of the way! Introducing Prompts - Hardcover 🇺🇦 Support Ukraine Hardcover Hardcover Open main menu Blog Twitter Discord Contact Supporters App Go to app Introducing Prompts By Adam Fortuna 1 17 2022, 5:18:21 PM · 3 min read Prompts are They’re a new way to ask a question where readers can answer to find the best Today we’re launching a new area of Hardcover called Prompts . To put it simply, Prompts are Someone from the community can ask a book related question and anyone can answer Here’s an example with the question “ What were your favorite childhood books? “: The prompt of the week Once someone asks this question, anyone can go in an answer Once you’re logged in, you can answer this prompt with any number of Whether one book comes to mind or a hundred, you can fill those By default, the answer form will filter for only books you’ve marked as “read” on Hardcover (notice the little “Only show books you’ve finished” checkbox). This is helpful if you’re already tracking all of your books on Hardcover and want to see limited search Add your answers to this Once you’ve selected a book as an answer to this prompt, you have the option to write This will show up for anyone who looks into why this book is an Redwall is the first book that got me excited about Your answers to this will show up on the All Answers page for the prompt, but also on a page within your profile . You can link back to just your answers to this prompt if you want to share it, or check out someone elses prompt My answers to this question as shown on my By collecting a bunch of answers to this prompt from the community, Hardcover is able to see which books are answered the most This means we can show the top results from the across the In this case we’ve only just launched the Prompts, so there are only 3 readers so far (from those of us working on Hardcover). As more readers fill out their answers the overview will The overall results shows the top most answered books for this What’s most exciting about this to me is that this will be useful tomorrow, a year from now and For those who want a deeper dive into the answers, they can head over to the Books tab and see the top There are always people looking for answers to this question, and the community as a whole can help people find an answer in a way that an algorithm can’t. This is just the beginning of prompts right We have a bunch of ideas on what to do Show the most common answers in the last years? In the last year? Books written by women? By POC? By LGBTQ+ authors? What about showcasing peoples explanations of why they added a book in more places across the site? Today we’re launching Prompts! Each week we’ll have a new Prompt of the Week that shows up at the top of the Prompts page . As with any beta feature, I’m sure there are going to be some issues with 😅 If you run into a bug, find anything annoying, or have any thoughts on how to make Prompts better, feel free to email our team at . ← More from the blog Want to Read More? Adam Fortuna By Adam Fortuna 9 2021, 8:04:33 PM · 3 min read After a bunch of discussions with users we have an idea on what the social side of Hardcover will Want a sneak peak? So, is Hardcover a Social Network? Yes – or at least it can We’re building Hardcover with three different social options for you to choose from: Public – Your account is completely Anyone can see what books you’ve read, are reading, lists you create and activity on the Followers Only – Only people you follow can see your activity on Private – No one can view your You’re effectively a You can still follow people and see what they’re reading (if they let you), but no one will be able to see what you do on These settings will also be available at an individual book or list level . If you’re reading a book you don’t want to show off publicly, you can mark it as private and no one is the (Side note: When it was crazy popular I read “50 Shades of Gray” but didn’t track it on On Hardcover I’d track it as a “followers only” book). This is a similar social approach to Twitter, Instagram and This isn’t a friendship like Facebook, but a follower model where anyone can follow anyone and see their public activity (or followers only activity if that user follows you). We’re building a second setting as well that determines who can interact with your activity on the You may decide to have a public account, but only allow comments and likes from your followers (or disable that altogether).
